# Test fixtures

Tests must be self-standing. Do not load or reference files under `docs/samples/`.

- Define render JSON, legend data, and other inputs inline in the test file, or in a dedicated `test/fixtures/` module.
- `docs/samples/` is for human documentation and may change independently of test expectations.
- When a sample documents behaviour you want to test, copy the relevant structure into a test fixture instead of importing the sample.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — couples tests to documentation samples
const sample = require("../docs/samples/formatting-mixed-patterns.json");
expect(ajv.validate(schema, sample)).to.equal(true);

// ✅ GOOD — fixture lives with the test
const mixedPatternsFixture: APRenderRep = {
    board: { style: "squares", height: 2, width: 2 },
    legend: { /* ... */ },
    pieces: "P1,P2\nFIXED,LIGHT",
};
expect(ajv.validate(schema, mixedPatternsFixture)).to.equal(true);
```
